    "headline": "Ex-Meta AI chief Yann LeCun's AMI raises $1.03 billion for alternative AI approach",
    "summary": "Advanced Machine Intelligence, the startup founded by former Meta Platforms chief AI scientist Yann LeCun, said on Tuesday it ‌raised $1.03 billion based on a $3.50 billion pre-money valuation, as it seeks ‌to commercialize artificial intelligence systems built around reasoning, planning and \"world models.\"  The funding round was co-led by Cathay Innovation, Greycroft, Hiro Capital, HV Capital and Bezos Expeditions.  Meanwhile, Meta has been intensifying its push into LLM ‌development.",
